HEADWORD: Elisor
<hw>E*li"sor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧liseur</ets>, fr. <ets>⟦eacute⟧lire</ets> to choose, L.
<ets>eligere</ets>. See <er>Elect</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>An elector or chooser; one of two persons appointed by a court to
return a jury or serve a writ when the sheriff and the coroners are
disqualified.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

